{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848079478,"sessionID":"ses_2873782adfferdluqTqD82CWpe","part":{"id":"prt_d78cb402d001mwrG2R98tSSdYn","messageID":"msg_d78c93428001d4kA655FdZQEek","sessionID":"ses_2873782adfferdluqTqD82CWpe","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-f023e5a0c1e5402aa8da88910c46f755","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Spec: AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n\n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the Sandbox Garbage Collector that periodically scans and deletes expired and idle sandboxes. The GC runs as a background goroutine with configurable intervals, enforces TTL via `ExpiresAt` timestamps, handles idle timeout cleanup via `LastActivity`, and limits batch operations to prevent cluster overload.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: GarbageCollector type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `GarbageCollector` as a background process for periodic sandbox cleanup.\n\n#### Scenario: GarbageCollector struct definition\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `GarbageCollector` struct\n- **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n  - `manager *SandboxLifecycleManager` for sandbox deletion delegation\n  - `interval time.Duration` for GC cycle interval\n  - `onceTimeout time.Duration` for single GC cycle timeout\n  - `stopCh chan struct{}` for graceful shutdown signal\n  - `wg sync.WaitGroup` for goroutine synchronization\n  - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n  - `idleTimeout time.Duration` for idle sandbox cleanup threshold\n  - `idleMu sync.RWMutex` for idleTimeout concurrent access protection\n\n#### Scenario: NewGarbageCollector constructor\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n- **WHEN** calling `NewGarbageCollector(manager, interval, onceTimeout, logger)`\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `*GarbageCollector` with:\n  - `interval` defaulted to `GarbageCollectorInterval` (2 minutes) if zero\n  - `onceTimeout` defaulted to `2 * time.Minute` if zero\n  - `idleTimeout` initialized from `manager.config.DefaultIdleTimeout`\n  - `stopCh` initialized as `make(chan struct{})`\n\n#### Scenario: NewGarbageCollector with custom interval\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n- **WHEN** calling `NewGarbageCollector(manager, 5*time.Minute, 3*time.Minute, logger)`\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `*GarbageCollector` with:\n  - `interval` = `5 * time.Minute`\n  - `onceTimeout` = `3 * time.Minute`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: GarbageCollector lifecycle\n\nThe system SHALL provide Start/Stop lifecycle methods for the GC background goroutine.\n\n#### Scenario: Start launches runLoop\n- **GIVEN** a `GarbageCollector` instance\n- **WHEN** calling `gc.Start()`\n- **THEN** `gc.wg.Add(1)` SHALL be called\n- AND `gc.runLoop()` SHALL be launched as a goroutine\n\n#### Scenario: Stop signals shutdown\n- **GIVEN** a running `GarbageCollector`\n- **WHEN** calling `gc.Stop()`\n- **THEN** `close(gc.stopCh)` SHALL be called\n- AND `gc.wg.Wait()` SHALL block until goroutine completes\n\n#### Scenario: runLoop initial execution\n- **GIVEN** a started `GarbageCollector`\n- **WHEN** `runLoop` begins\n- **THEN** `gc.runOnce(context.Background())` SHALL be called immediately\n- AND ticker SHALL be created with `time.NewTicker(gc.interval)`\n\n#### Scenario: runLoop ticker-driven execution\n- **GIVEN** a running `runLoop`\n- **WHEN** ticker fires\n- **THEN** `gc.runOnce(context.Background())` SHALL be called\n\n#### Scenario: runLoop stops on stopCh\n- **GIVEN** a running `runLoop`\n- **WHEN** `stopCh` receives signal\n- **THEN** `gc.logger.Info(\"garbage collector stopped\")` SHALL be called\n- AND goroutine SHALL return\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: runOnce GC cycle\n\nThe system SHALL implement `runOnce` for a single garbage collection cycle.\n\n#### Scenario: runOnce with context timeout\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n- **WHEN** calling `runOnce(ctx)`\n- **THEN** `context.WithTimeout(ctx, gc.onceTimeout)` SHALL be created\n- AND cancel SHALL be deferred\n\n#### Scenario: runOnce queries expired sandboxes\n- **GIVEN** `runOnce` execution\n- **WHEN** listing sandboxes for cleanup\n- **THEN** `gc.manager.store.ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, now, GCBatchSize)` SHALL be called\n- AND result SHALL be limited to `GCBatchSize=16`\n\n#### Scenario: runOnce queries inactive sandboxes\n- **GIVEN** `runOnce` execution\n- **WHEN** listing sandboxes for cleanup\n- **THEN** `inactiveBefore = now.Add(-idleTimeout)` SHALL be computed\n- AND `gc.manager.store.ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, inactiveBefore, GCBatchSize)` SHALL be called\n\n#### Scenario: runOnce deletes expired sandbox\n- **GIVEN** an expired sandbox with `ExpiresAt < now`\n- **WHEN** `runOnce` processes it\n- **THEN** `gc.manager.DeleteSandbox(ctx, sb.SessionID)` SHALL be called\n- AND deletion reason SHALL be `DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached`\n\n#### Scenario: runOnce deletes inactive sandbox\n- **GIVEN** an inactive sandbox with `LastActivity < inactiveBefore`\n- **WHEN** `runOnce` processes it\n- **THEN** `gc.manager.DeleteSandbox(ctx, sb.SessionID)` SHALL be called\n- AND deletion reason SHALL be `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout`\n\n#### Scenario: runOnce ignores NotFound error\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox that no longer exists\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandbox` returns `NotFoundError`\n- **THEN** error SHALL be ignored with `continue`\n\n#### Scenario: runOnce logs deletion success\n- **GIVEN** a successfully deleted sandbox\n- **WHEN** deletion completes\n- **THEN** `gc.logger.Info(\"gc deleted sandbox\", \"sessionID\", ..., \"sandboxName\", ..., \"reason\", ...)` SHALL be called\n\n#### Scenario: runOnce logs deletion failure\n- **GIVEN** a deletion that fails (not NotFound)\n- **WHEN** error occurs\n- **THEN** `gc.logger.Error(\"gc delete failed\", \"sessionID\", ..., \"err\", ...)` SHALL be called\n- AND processing SHALL continue for remaining sandboxes\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Batch size limitation\n\nThe system SHALL limit cleanup operations per cycle to prevent cluster overload.\n\n#### Scenario: GCBatchSize constant\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n- **WHEN** reading constants\n- **THEN** `GCBatchSize` SHALL be `16`\n\n#### Scenario: ListExpiredSandboxes respects limit\n- **GIVEN** `MemoryStore.ListExpiredSandboxes`\n- **WHEN** calling with `limit=16`\n- **THEN** result SHALL be truncated to at most `16` sandboxes\n- AND sandboxes SHALL be sorted by `ExpiresAt` ascending\n\n#### Scenario: ListInactiveSandboxes respects limit\n- **GIVEN** `MemoryStore.ListInactiveSandboxes`\n- **WHEN** calling with `limit=16`\n- **THEN** result SHALL be truncated to at most `16` sandboxes\n- AND sandboxes SHALL be sorted by `LastActivity` ascending\n\n#### Scenario: Combined batch limit\n- **GIVEN** 20 expired and 20 inactive sandboxes\n- **WHEN** `runOnce` executes\n- **THEN** at most `16 + 16 = 32` sandboxes SHALL be processed\n- AND remaining sandboxes SHALL be processed in subsequent cycles\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Store interface extensions\n\nThe system SHALL extend the Store interface with GC-specific query methods.\n\n#### Scenario: Store interface includes GC methods\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `Store` interface\n- **THEN** interface SHALL include:\n  - `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n  - `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n\n#### Scenario: MemoryStore ListExpiredSandboxes implementation\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go`\n- **WHEN** calling `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)`\n- **THEN** all sandboxes with `ExpiresAt.Before(before)` SHALL be returned\n- AND result SHALL be sorted by `ExpiresAt` ascending\n- AND result SHALL be limited to `limit` entries\n\n#### Scenario: MemoryStore ListInactiveSandboxes implementation\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go`\n- **WHEN** calling `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)`\n- **THEN** all sandboxes with non-zero `LastActivity` and `LastActivity.Before(before)` SHALL be returned\n- AND result SHALL be sorted by `LastActivity` ascending\n- AND result SHALL be limited to `limit` entries\n\n#### Scenario: ListInactiveSandboxes skips zero LastActivity\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with `LastActivity.IsZero() == true`\n- **WHEN** calling `ListInactiveSandboxes`\n- **THEN** that sandbox SHALL NOT be included in results\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Runtime configuration\n\nThe system SHALL support runtime configuration of GC parameters.\n\n#### Scenario: SetIdleTimeout method\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n- **WHEN** calling `gc.SetIdleTimeout(30 * time.Minute)`\n- **THEN** `gc.idleMu.Lock()` SHALL be acquired\n- AND `gc.idleTimeout` SHALL be updated to `30 * time.Minute`\n- AND mutex SHALL be released\n\n#### Scenario: getIdleTimeout method\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n- **WHEN** calling `gc.getIdleTimeout()`\n- **THEN** `gc.idleMu.RLock()` SHALL be acquired\n- AND current `idleTimeout` value SHALL be returned\n- AND mutex SHALL be released\n\n#### Scenario: GetStats method\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n- **WHEN** calling `gc.GetStats()`\n- **THEN** `GarbageCollectorStats` SHALL be returned with:\n  - `Interval`: current GC cycle interval\n  - `OnceTimeout`: current single-cycle timeout\n  - `IdleTimeout`: current idle threshold\n\n#### Scenario: GarbageCollectorStats struct\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n- **WHEN** reading `GarbageCollectorStats`\n- **THEN** struct SHALL contain:\n  - `Interval time.Duration`\n  - `OnceTimeout time.Duration`\n  - `IdleTimeout time.Duration`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Deletion reason determination\n\nThe system SHALL categorize deletion reasons for logging and tracking.\n\n#### Scenario: determineDeletionReason function\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n- **WHEN** calling `determineDeletionReason(sandbox, now, idleTimeout)`\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `DeletionReason`\n\n#### Scenario: MaxDurationReached reason\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with `now.After(sandbox.ExpiresAt)`\n- **WHEN** determining reason\n- **THEN** `DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached` SHALL be returned\n\n#### Scenario: IdleTimeout reason\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with non-zero `LastActivity` and `now.After(sandbox.LastActivity.Add(idleTimeout))`\n- **WHEN** determining reason and `ExpiresAt` not yet reached\n- **THEN** `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout` SHALL be returned\n\n#### Scenario: UserRequest fallback reason\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox not expired and not idle\n- **WHEN** determining reason\n- **THEN** `DeletionReasonUserRequest` SHALL be returned as fallback\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: DeletionReason constants\n\nThe system SHALL define deletion reason constants for categorization.\n\n#### Scenario: DeletionReasonIdleTimeout constant\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n- **WHEN** reading constants\n- **THEN** `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout` SHALL be `\"IdleTimeout\"`\n\n#### Scenario: DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached constant\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n- **WHEN** reading constants\n- **THEN** `DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached` SHALL be `\"MaxDurationReached\"`\n\n#### Scenario: DeletionReasonUserRequest constant\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n- **WHEN** reading constants\n- **THEN** `DeletionReasonUserRequest` SHALL be `\"UserRequest\"`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Default constants\n\nThe system SHALL define default timeout constants.\n\n#### Scenario: GarbageCollectorInterval constant\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n- **WHEN** reading constants\n- **THEN** `GarbageCollectorInterval` SHALL be `2 * time.Minute`\n\n#### Scenario: DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout constant\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n- **WHEN** reading constants\n- **THEN** `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` SHALL be `15 * time.Minute`\n\n#### Scenario: DefaultSandboxTTL constant\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n- **WHEN** reading constants\n- **THEN** `DefaultSandboxTTL` SHALL be `8 * time.Hour`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Concurrent safety\n\nThe system SHALL handle concurrent access safely.\n\n#### Scenario: idleMu protects idleTimeout\n- **GIVEN** `GarbageCollector` with `idleMu sync.RWMutex`\n- **WHEN** concurrent reads/writes to `idleTimeout`\n- **THEN** `sync.RWMutex` SHALL prevent race conditions\n- AND `RLock` SHALL be used for reads\n- AND `Lock` SHALL be used for writes\n\n#### Scenario: Store mutex protection\n- **GIVEN** `MemoryStore` with `sync.RWMutex`\n- **WHEN** concurrent `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`\n- **THEN** `sync.RWMutex` SHALL prevent race conditions\n\n#### Scenario: runOnce called from single goroutine\n- **GIVEN** `runLoop` design\n- **WHEN** GC is running\n- **THEN** `runOnce` SHALL only be called from the single `runLoop` goroutine\n- AND no concurrent `runOnce` calls SHALL occur from GC itself\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Deletion delegation\n\nThe system SHALL delegate actual deletion to SandboxLifecycleManager.\n\n#### Scenario: DeleteSandbox delegation\n- **GIVEN** `runOnce` processing a sandbox\n- **WHEN** calling deletion\n- **THEN** `gc.manager.DeleteSandbox(ctx, sessionID)` SHALL be called\n- AND deletion SHALL handle both K8s CR deletion and store cleanup\n\n#### Scenario: DeleteSandbox handles K8s resources\n- **GIVEN** `SandboxLifecycleManager.DeleteSandbox`\n- **WHEN** deletion executes\n- **THEN** `SandboxGVR` (agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1/sandboxes) SHALL be deleted\n- AND `SandboxClaimGVR` SHALL be deleted if `Kind == SandboxClaimKind`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Integration with HTTPServer\n\nThe system SHALL integrate GC with the HTTPServer lifecycle.\n\n#### Scenario: GC created in HTTPServer\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go`\n- **WHEN** HTTPServer is initialized\n- **THEN** `NewGarbageCollector` SHALL be called with:\n  - `manager` = `SandboxLifecycleManager`\n  - `interval` = `config.GCInterval`\n  - `onceTimeout` = `config.GCOnceTimeout`\n  - `logger` = server logger\n\n#### Scenario: GC started on server start\n- **GIVEN** HTTPServer with GC\n- **WHEN** server starts\n- **THEN** `gc.Start()` SHALL be called\n\n#### Scenario: GC stopped on server shutdown\n- **GIVEN** running HTTPServer with GC\n- **WHEN** server shuts down\n- **THEN** `gc.Stop()` SHALL be called\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Unit tests for GarbageCollector\n\nThe system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for GC behavior.\n\n#### Scenario: TestNewGarbageCollector\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Constructor returns valid instance\n  - Custom interval and timeout are set correctly\n\n#### Scenario: TestNewGarbageCollector_DefaultInterval\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n- **WHEN** calling `NewGarbageCollector(manager, 0, 0, logger)`\n- **THEN** default values SHALL be applied:\n  - `interval` = `GarbageCollectorInterval`\n  - `onceTimeout` = `2 * time.Minute`\n\n#### Scenario: TestGarbageCollector_StartStop\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - `Start()` launches goroutine\n  - `Stop()` completes without hanging\n  - Goroutine exits cleanly\n\n#### Scenario: TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Expired\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests with expired sandbox\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Expired sandbox is deleted\n  - Active sandbox remains\n\n#### Scenario: TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Inactive\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests with inactive sandbox\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Inactive sandbox (LastActivity > idleTimeout ago) is deleted\n  - Active sandbox remains\n\n#### Scenario: TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Limit\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests with 20 expired sandboxes\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - At most `GCBatchSize=16` sandboxes are deleted per cycle\n\n#### Scenario: TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_ContinueOnError\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - All sandboxes are processed even if some deletions fail\n\n#### Scenario: TestGarbageCollector_GetStats\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - `GetStats()` returns correct interval, timeout, idleTimeout\n  - `SetIdleTimeout()` updates stats correctly\n\n#### Scenario: TestGarbageCollector_ConcurrentRunOnce\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests with concurrent `runOnce` calls\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Store handles concurrent access safely\n  - No race conditions occur\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Integration tests for GC\n\nThe system SHALL have integration tests verifying GC with lifecycle manager.\n\n#### Scenario: Full GC flow test\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - GC deletes expired sandboxes\n  - Store is updated after deletion\n  - Multiple GC cycles process remaining sandboxes\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Error handling\n\nThe system SHALL handle errors gracefully in GC operations.\n\n#### Scenario: ListExpiredSandboxes error\n- **GIVEN** `runOnce` execution\n- **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes` returns error\n- **THEN** `gc.logger.Error(\"failed to list expired sandboxes\", \"err\", err)` SHALL be called\n- AND `runOnce` SHALL return error\n\n#### Scenario: ListInactiveSandboxes error\n- **GIVEN** `runOnce` execution\n- **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes` returns error\n- **THEN** `gc.logger.Error(\"failed to list inactive sandboxes\", \"err\", err)` SHALL be called\n- AND `runOnce` SHALL return error\n\n#### Scenario: DeleteSandbox NotFound handling\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox already deleted\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandbox` returns `NotFoundError`\n- **THEN** error SHALL be silently ignored\n- AND GC SHALL continue to next sandbox\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: File structure\n\nThe system SHALL organize GC files correctly.\n\n#### Scenario: garbage_collector.go location\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n- **WHEN** listing files\n- **THEN** `garbage_collector.go` SHALL exist with:\n  - `GarbageCollector` struct\n  - `NewGarbageCollector` constructor\n  - `Start`, `Stop`, `runLoop`, `runOnce` methods\n  - `SetIdleTimeout`, `getIdleTimeout`, `GetStats` methods\n  - `GCBatchSize` constant\n  - `GarbageCollectorStats` struct\n\n#### Scenario: garbage_collector_test.go location\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n- **WHEN** listing files\n- **THEN** `garbage_collector_test.go` SHALL exist with unit tests\n\n#### Scenario: store.go with GC methods\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go`\n- **WHEN** reading file\n- **THEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `ListInactiveSandboxes` SHALL be implemented\n\n#### Scenario: types.go with Store interface\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n- **WHEN** reading `Store` interface\n- **THEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `ListInactiveSandboxes` SHALL be declared\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: LifecycleConfig integration\n\nThe system SHALL use LifecycleConfig for GC configuration.\n\n#### Scenario: LifecycleConfig GC fields\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n- **WHEN** reading `LifecycleConfig`\n- **THEN** struct SHALL contain:\n  - `GCInterval time.Duration`\n  - `GCOnceTimeout time.Duration`\n  - `DefaultIdleTimeout time.Duration`\n\n#### Scenario: DefaultLifecycleConfig GC defaults\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n- **WHEN** calling `DefaultLifecycleConfig()`\n- **THEN** returned config SHALL have:\n  - `GCInterval` = `GarbageCollectorInterval` (2 minutes)\n  - `GCOnceTimeout` = `2 * time.Minute`\n  - `DefaultIdleTimeout` = `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` (15 minutes)\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` | GarbageCollector implementation with Start/Stop/runOnce |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go` | Unit tests for GC behavior |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go` | ListExpiredSandboxes/ListInactiveSandboxes implementations |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` | Store interface extensions, DeletionReason constants |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go` | determineDeletionReason, LifecycleConfig GC fields |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | GarbageCollectorInterval, DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout constants |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `context` | Context with timeout for GC cycles |\n| `sync` | WaitGroup, RWMutex for concurrency |\n| `time` | Duration, Ticker, Now for timing |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo struct |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apierrors` | IsNotFound error checking |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | DeleteOptions |\n\n---\n\n## GC Flow Diagram\n\n```\nGarbageCollector\n│\n├── Start()\n│   └── wg.Add(1)\n│   └── go runLoop()\n│       ├── runOnce(ctx) [immediate]\n│       ├── ticker := NewTicker(interval)\n│       ├── select { stopCh, ticker.C }\n│       │   ├── ticker.C → runOnce(ctx)\n│       │   └── stopCh → return\n│       └── wg.Done()\n│\n├── Stop()\n│   ├── close(stopCh)\n│   └── wg.Wait()\n│\n└── runOnce(ctx)\n    ├── ctx, cancel := WithTimeout(ctx, onceTimeout)\n    ├── expired := ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, now, GCBatchSize)\n    ├── inactiveBefore := now.Add(-idleTimeout)\n    ├── inactive := ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, inactiveBefore, GCBatchSize)\n    ├── for sb in expired + inactive:\n    │   ├── DeleteSandbox(ctx, sb.SessionID)\n    │   ├── reason := determineDeletionReason(sb, now, idleTimeout)\n    │   └── logger.Info(\"gc deleted sandbox\", ...)\n    └── return nil\n```\n\n---\n\n## Configuration Values\n\n| Parameter | Default | Configurable | Source |\n|-----------|---------|--------------|--------|\n| `interval` | 2m | Yes | `NewGarbageCollector` param |\n| `onceTimeout` | 2m | Yes | `NewGarbageCollector` param |\n| `idleTimeout` | 15m | Yes (runtime) | `SetIdleTimeout` |\n| `batchSize` | 16 | No (const) | `GCBatchSize` |\n\n---\n\n## Deletion Reasons\n\n| Reason | Condition | Description |\n|--------|-----------|-------------|\n| `IdleTimeout` | `LastActivity + idleTimeout < now` AND `ExpiresAt > now` | Sandbox inactive for too long |\n| `MaxDurationReached` | `ExpiresAt < now` | Sandbox exceeded maximum TTL |\n| `UserRequest` | Neither above | Fallback for manual deletion |\n\n---\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] GarbageCollector struct defined with all required fields\n- [ ] NewGarbageCollector constructor with default fallbacks\n- [ ] Start() launches background goroutine\n- [ ] Stop() signals shutdown and waits for completion\n- [ ] runLoop uses ticker for periodic execution\n- [ ] runOnce has context timeout protection\n- [ ] ListExpiredSandboxes queries expired by ExpiresAt\n- [ ] ListInactiveSandboxes queries inactive by LastActivity\n- [ ] Batch limit (GCBatchSize=16) enforced per query\n- [ ] NotFound errors silently ignored\n- [ ] Deletion errors logged but don't stop cycle\n- [ ] determineDeletionReason categorizes deletions correctly\n- [ ] SetIdleTimeout runtime configuration supported\n- [ ] GetStats returns current configuration\n- [ ] idleMu protects concurrent idleTimeout access\n- [ ] Store interface includes GC query methods\n- [ ] MemoryStore implements GC query methods\n- [ ] LifecycleConfig includes GC parameters\n- [ ] DefaultLifecycleConfig provides GC defaults\n- [ ] Unit tests cover expired/inactive/batch scenarios\n- [ ] Unit tests cover concurrent safety\n- [ ] Integration tests verify full GC flow\n- [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n- [ ] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n- [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/store.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/go.mod":[{"range":{"start":{"line":49,"character":49},"end":{"line":49,"character":60}},"severity":2,"source":"go mod tidy","message":"k8s.io/utils should be direct"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/config_test.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":37,"character":14},"end":{"line":37,"character":14}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field WriteTimeout"},{"range":{"start":{"line":38,"character":13},"end":{"line":38,"character":13}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field IdleTimeout"},{"range":{"start":{"line":39,"character":17},"end":{"line":39,"character":17}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.